Recursion is when a function calls itself to solve a smaller version of the same problem.

Think of it like Russian nesting dolls. Each doll opens to reveal a smaller identical doll inside, until you reach one that does not open — that is your base case.

function countdown(n) {
  if (n === 0) return;
  console.log(n);
  countdown(n - 1);
}

The function keeps calling itself with n-1 until it hits zero. Without a base case it calls itself forever — stack overflow.
